msContents.summary: Commentary on the summary of arithmetical operations by the late 13th- and early 14th-century scholar Ibn al-Bannāʼ. Demonstrates with examples the calculation of sums involving fractional numbers and square roots. Extensive marginal notes on a few leaves (p. 20-35). The first leaf is missing and the text ends abruptly. Several leaves have restored outer margins. Pages 189-194 missing text because of conservation after water damage.

msItem.title: Ḥaṭṭ al-niqāb ʻan wujūh aʻmāl al-ḥisāb.
[حط النقاب عن وجوه اعمال الحساب]

author.persName: Ibn al-Qunfudh, Aḥmad ibn Ḥusayn, ǂd -1406 or 1407
ابن القنفذ، أحمد بن حسين، ǂd -1406 or 1407

support.watermark: Laid European paper with grape watermark.

supportDesc.extent: 159 leaves : 268 x 195 (205 x 135) mm bound to 274 x 208 mm
supportDesc.foliation: 159 leaves; [1-55, i-ii, 56-151, i-ii, 152-165, 164-273, 174-179, 280-312], later pagination in blue ink, upper center. Catchwords on each leaf, lower left verso, many obscured by past water damage.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in maghribi script in brown ink; pointed. Headings in larger script.

binding.p: Later red leather, blind-stamped with central mandorla, two pendants on the vertical axis, cornerpieces and frame; rebacked. Marbled doublure.

origin.p: Written in northern Africa, probably Morocco, in the 15th or 16th century.

history.provenance: Sold by Sam Fogg Ltd. (London) to Lawrence J. Schoenberg, July 2004.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2013.
